            "answer_text": "A2A. Sigh! I do not understand this obsession with the caste of bygone rulers. They lived in a time when the caste system was pretty much fluid. When you are as powerful an autocrat as Ashoka, your subjects wouldn\u2019t dare ask this if they valued their life. If you really want to know, know that the Mauryas were ostensibly the Moriyas of Pippalivana, a kshatriya clan related to the Shakya clan (does the term Shakyamuni ring any bells?) Read this: Shivaprasad P's answer to What was the Mauryan Dynasty? ",
